CAPE TOWN - Cricket South Africa on Monday morning confirmed that paceman Dale Steyn will be out of action for at least six weeks. Steyn suffered a heel injury on Saturday at Newlands where South Africa are hosting India in the first Test. READ: Dale Steyn comeback overshadowed by injury The note from Cricket South Africa reads: "The foot and ankle specialist confirmed the extent and nature of the injury. He is unable to do much at the moment so he will be reassessed in 4 – 6 weeks." "He will follow a management and rehab plan once he is out of the moon boot but he is definitely out of the India Series."
	  African News Agency